				 Bar on boy doc parents
																								Chennai, Oct. 31: The doctor-couple who allowed their son to perform a Caesarean section so that the 15-year-old could make it to the Guinness World Records were today temporarily barred from practice.																								The licences of Dr K. Murugesan and Gandhimathi, who run the Mathi Surgical and Maternity Hospital in Manaparai, 40km from Tiruchirappalli, have been suspended. They were arrested on June 25, days after the scandal rocked the state and the countrys medical fraternity.																								The Tamil Nadu Medical Council, an affiliate of the Indian Medical Council, has clamped the curbs for a year, but its possibly the first time that the body has taken such strong action against a member. 
